text.paragraph:
A small proportion of women will have persistent hypertriglyceridemia while on the pill. As discussed earlier (see WARNINGS 1a 
                           and 1d
                           ), changes in serum triglycerides and lipoprotein levels have been reported in oral contraceptive users.

An increased risk of the following serious adverse reactions has been associated with the use of oral contraceptives (See 
                        WARNINGS
                     ).
